    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nUser may not know when it's time to run `:checkhealth`. Not all health status change seems to appear at the Nvim start (especially if a plugin is lazy or manually loaded).\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nProvide a way to notify user if the health status changed.\n\nI think a new autocommand event (e.g. `HealthChanged`) containing the provider name, level, etc. could be the basis for more flexible usage (e.g. lazy updating of some user-defined status variable or selection what to ignore on the user side). This way would be enough to warn of a new error on user demand. ",
    "closed_at": "2025-09-07T17:02:26Z",
