            "body": "@justinmk Your proposal seems to require more changes that I had not considered at all. FYI: please reopen and change this issue if needed. \n\nI started with (probably wrong) assumption that some errors are added at runtime. It appears that this is not the case of the `vim.health` interface. For example, `vim.deprecate()` can collect such warnings at runtime, but `add()` is only a method specific for that module.",
